    "## So, where are you? Locating your working directory\n",
    "now, we will use the 'here' function in the 'here' package to do this.\n",
    "* The here() function in R helps you locate files and directories in a project in a reliable and reproducible way. It is particularly useful for avoiding issues with file paths when working across different systems or environments.\n",
    "* Note that the output of the 'here' function is of character type. In other words, it will print out the root folder path, not link you to the path (see more next)"
   ]
  },
